word_mean_info__list.difference: 指任何种类的工作，也泛指职业。
较正式用词，语气庄重，指长期从事，但不一定以此为主计的职业。
泛指任何一种职业，既不分什么行业，也不管是脑力还是体力劳动。
指受雇于他人，领取工资以谋生计，有较固定工作的职业。
指需要有熟练技巧、技能和体力的职业。
以前常指要受过高等教育(尤指法律、医学和神学)才能获得的职业，现在一般指为谋生日的职业，尤指从事脑力劳动和受过专门训练，具有某种专业知识的职业。
指经过专门训练，终身愿意从事的职业。
通常指一切有收入，不分脑力与体力运动，不论是否有技艺的长期或临时的职业。

bilingual.source: Yes, and you have found the career that suits your talents.
bilingual.target: 是的，你找到了适合你才能的职业。

bilingual.source: The only thing I don't like about this career is that you can get very sad when animals die.
bilingual.target: 我唯一不喜欢这份职业的是，当动物死去时你会非常难过。

bilingual.source: Through career planning, you can better understand your career goals.
bilingual.target: 通过职业规划，你可以更好地了解自己的职业目标。
我的职业生涯刚刚开始。

bilingual.source: He decided to change over his career.

list.abstract: career是一个英语单词，可以用作名词、形容词和不及物动词。常用意思为生涯、职业、全速等。

yingyinNormal.en: And the other half of the Career Pack, Brutus and Enobaria. What's with her teeth?
yingyinNormal.zh: 职业组的另一半，布鲁托和伊诺贝丽，从小就是职业选手。她的牙怎么了？

yingyinNormal.en: I've made a career out of dealing with problematic parts of the world.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的职业就是处理世界的问题地区。

yingyinNormal.en: Your career and your life will have starts and stops and zigs and zags.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的职业和生活会有始终，会有曲折。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《Facebook COO谢丽尔·桑德伯格哈佛演讲》

yingyinNormal.en: Do you have aspirations for a career, or a professional dream that you wish to pursue?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你有没有想要从事的事业想要实现的职业梦想？

yingyinNormal.en: This is the single greatest day of my professional career. Gunther. Six glasses.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是我职业生涯中最伟大的一天。冈瑟,，6个杯子。

yingyinNormal.en: That's it? You're gonna let me do this? This is my career we're talking about here!
yingyinNormal.zh: 就这样？你真要让我这样做？这事关我的职业生涯耶。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, very nice. Good for you guys. So this is what career day is really all about.
yingyinNormal.zh: 挺好，你们这样挺好，这才是职业日这个活动的真谛所在。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, well, I'm kinda heading in a new career direction and you know, you gotta start at the bottom. Dude.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我在转换职业跑道中，得要从基层做起。老兄。

yingyinNormal.en: He'll have his arm around Peter at the biggest moment of his career. That'll leave a mark.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在他职业生涯中最重要的一刻，他会紧密跟随彼得，这必会留下污点。

yingyinNormal.en: But the book. My entire career. It's all based on a lie. You don't have a monopoly on secrets.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但那本书，我整个职业生涯，都是基于一个谎言。秘密不是你一个人的专属。

yingyinNormal.en: You gave your own father an experimental drug. I could finish your career with one phone call.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你给自己的父亲用上了实验中的药物，我一个电话就可以结束你的职业生涯。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Rise of the Planet of the Apes》

yingyinNormal.en: This gun was illegally obtained by a career criminal at a gun show where background checks aren't mandatory.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这把枪是一个职业罪犯非法地在一个不强制背景审查的枪展上购得的。

yingyinNormal.en: Your monkey found a new career, in the entertainment field. That's all I know. This is unbelievable.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的猴子有了新职业了，往娱乐界发展去了，我只知道这一些。真是令人难以置信。

yingyinNormal.en: Are you kidding me? You've set my career back at least two years, and you think you can make it right with I'm sorry?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你开什么玩笑？你害得我的职业发展倒退了至少两年，你觉得说句抱歉就能算了吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, well, do you want to go? Of course not. I'm a theoretical physicist. A career I chose in no small part because it's indoors.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你想去吗？当然不想，我是理论物理学家，我选这个职业完全出于能在家办公。

yingyinNormal.en: All right, future history makers, welcome to career day. Now there are a lot of ways to make your mark on the world.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好的，未来的历史缔造者们，欢迎来到职业日。你们能在这个世界留下痕迹的方式有很多种。

yingyinNormal.en: No. Well, I like the idea of art, the beauty. But only in the right context. Just not as a career. I don't have the necessary talents.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，呃，我欣赏艺术的理念，还有它的美，但只是在特定的条件下，但我不想把它当成职业，我自知没有那方面的天分。

yingyinNormal.en: I've done over 35,000 interviews in my career. and as soon as that camera shuts off, everyone always turns to be and inevitably in their own way ask this question: Was that okay?
yingyinNormal.zh: 在我的职业生涯中，曾经做过35000次访谈，每当摄影机关掉的时候，所有的受访者必然会用自己的方式问出这样一个问题：我表现得还可以吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, that's it. I hate to be the feminist here, between the two of us, but you should be able to have a huge career and be who you are without having to accept that your husband is having an affair as some kind of payback.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了，没了。我不想再我们俩之间做支持女权的那个，但你应该拥有一个好的职业，做你自己，别就认为你丈夫出轨是对你的报复

yingyinNormal.en: This kind of experience happens to everyone. It will happen to you. You will lose something, or someone you think you can't live without. Or you will suffer a terrible illness or injury, or your career will fall apart before your eyes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没有人能幸免这种事。它会发生在你身上。你会失去一切失去不能失去的人。或者会遭受严重的疾病或伤害，或者眼见着自己的职业生涯分崩离析。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: an occupation undertaken for a significant period of a person's life and with opportunities for progress

examination_example.sentence: According to the <highlight>career</highlight> counselors and experts who study them, Generation Zs are clear-eyed, economic pragmatists.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据职业顾问和研究他们的专家的说法，Z世代是目光敏锐的经济实用主义者。

examination_example.sentence: A fifth grader gets a homework assignment to select his future <highlight>career</highlight> path from a list of occupations.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一个五年级学生拿到一份家庭作业：从职业列表中选择他未来的职业道路。

examination_example.sentence: G. I. Joe had a distinguished <highlight>career</highlight> fighting German, Japanese, and Korean troops.
examination_example.sentence_trans: G. I. Joe在抗击德国、日本和朝鲜军队的战斗中拥有辉煌的军旅生涯。

word_usage.usage:
表示“工作”
career指从事的职业或希望毕生从事的事业。
work既可指体力劳动也可指脑力劳动，通常都以挣钱为目的，有时也指机器干的工作。
job多用于口语，侧重指受雇用的、以谋生为目的的工作。
profession指需要专门技能（尤其是较高教育水平）的职业、专业。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 意为“生涯”，常指终身从事的工作或职业。
意为“职业、行业、专业”，正式用语，指受高等教育和特别训练的工作。
意为“工作、事儿”，可数名词。
意为“工作、事儿”，为不可数名词。
意为“职业、行业、专业”，正式用语。
意为“职业、岗位”，一般指某种特定工作。
意为“行当、行业、手艺”，尤指需要技术性劳动的工作。
意为“行业、（职业正规的）工作、（赖以为生的）正业”，尤指一个人特别适合或尤其有资格胜任的职业。

examination_example.sentence: Employees will be offered a <highlight>career</highlight> that is even more fulfilling and more rewarding.

examination_example.sentence: It may adversely affect his future <highlight>career</highlight> prospects.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这可能会对他未来的职业前程产生不利影响。

examination_example.sentence: It's the basis for healthy parenting, lasting friendships, <highlight>career</highlight> development, and so much more.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它是健康育儿、持久友谊、职业发展等等的基础。

examination_example.sentence: Her <highlight>career</highlight> as a botanist.

examination_example.sentence: Marconi's <highlight>career</highlight> was devoted to making wireless communication happen cheaply, efficiently, smoothly, and with an elegance.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 马可尼的职业生涯致力于使无线通信以廉价、高效、顺畅、优雅的方式进行。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: an occupation undertaken for a significant period of a person's life and with opportunities for progress

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Career</highlight> interruptions related to motherhood may make it harder for women to advance in their careers and compete for top executive jobs.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 生养孩子导致工作中断，这可能让女性难以在事业上更进一步，因而无力竞争高级管理职位。

examination_example.sentence: Current life structures, <highlight>career</highlight> paths, educational choices, and social norms are out of tune with the emerging reality of longer lifespans.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当前的生活结构、职业道路、教育选择和社会准则都与长寿这一日益显现的现实情况格格不入。

examination_example.sentence: Take, for instance, the age at which people make commitments such as buying a house, getting married, having children, or starting a <highlight>career</highlight>. These are all fundamental commitments that are now occurring later in life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 就拿人们履行买房、结婚、生育、或步入职场的责任的年龄为例。如今都在推迟履行这些基本责任。

examination_example.sentence: They tend to start their <highlight>careers</highlight> and family at the same age.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们往往在相同的年龄步入职场、组建家庭。

sense_info_list.en: the progress through history of an institution; organization; or others

examination_example.sentence: A multi-stage life will have profound changes not just in how you manage your <highlight>career</highlight>, but also in your approach to life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 多阶段的人生不仅会对你的职业生涯产生深远的影响，也会对你的生活方式产生深远的影响。

examination_example.sentence: It is impossible that a single shot of education, administered in childhood and early adulthood, will be able to support a sustained, 60-year <highlight>career</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在童年和成年早期所接受的一次性教育不可能支撑60年这么持久的职业生涯。

examination_example.sentence: It seems likely, then, that the traditional three-stage life will evolve into multiple stages containing two, three, or even more different <highlight>careers</highlight>. Each of these stages could potentially be different.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 那么，传统的三段式生活似乎很可能演变成包含两个、三个甚至更多不同职业生涯的多个生命阶段。每个阶段可能各不相同。

examination_example.sentence: At the starting line of their <highlight>careers</highlight>, they are better educated than their mothers and grandmothers had been — or than their young male counterparts are now.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在职业生涯的起跑线上，千禧一代的年轻女性和她们的母亲、祖母那代人相比受过更好的教育，或者与同属千禧一代的年轻男性相比，她们受过更好的教育。

examination_example.sentence: The Olympic got wrecked before the Titanic did, but it was the only one to survive and maintain a successful <highlight>career</highlight> of 24 years.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 奥林匹克号在泰坦尼克号遇难之前就已经失事，但它是唯一一艘幸存下来并成功维持了24年服役生涯的邮船。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: I was annoyed in that period and stopped practising, declaring I had reached the ceiling of my singing <highlight>career</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 那段时间我很恼火，于是停止了练习，宣称自己已经达到了歌唱生涯的顶峰。

examination_example.sentence: Did Nielsen then feel content in his <highlight>career</highlight>?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 尼尔森当时对自己的职业生涯感到满意吗？

examination_example.sentence: It wasn't until 1980—32 years into his <highlight>career</highlight>—that he landed the role it would seem he was made for in Airplane!
examination_example.sentence_trans: 直到1980年，也就是他职业生涯的第32年，他才在《空前绝后满天飞》中获得了一个看起来很适合他的角色！

examination_example.sentence: As working from home becomes increasingly common, people are finding it easier to combine parenthood with a full-time <highlight>career</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着在家工作变得越来越普遍，人们发现更容易将父母身份与全职工作结合起来。

examination_example.sentence: The admiration and respect his uncle earned inspired Nielsen to make a <highlight>career</highlight> (职业) in acting.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他叔叔所赢得的钦佩和尊重激励尼尔森投身表演事业。

examination_example.sentence: It inspires their creativity in designing their future <highlight>career</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这激发了他们设计未来职业的创造力。
